Although rosemary is a good substitute for any herb if you have no other option, there are more, better suited substitutions for rarer herbs.

The beauty about substitutions means you don’t have to own a huge collection of herbs. But when you substitute one for another, it’s always good to make sure that the herbs you choose have the same kind of magickal or medicinal properties as the ones being substituted. 

Have you got any good substitutions for harder to find herbs?

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
☘️ 𝔾𝕠𝕠𝕕 𝕃𝕦𝕔𝕜 𝕊𝕡𝕖𝕝𝕝 𝕁𝕒𝕣 ☘️
This spell jar is to help manifest good luck within your life. Whether you want luck in finding a job, prosperity in financial matters or just want an extra boost of luck within your life in general, this jar can help. 

This spell jar works better when created on a Thursday as this is the day which is associated with Jupiter, the planet of good luck. This is why the jar includes the symbol for Jupiter drawn on a small piece of paper. 

The clover can be a three leaf clover as this is still associated with good luck and fortune, although you can use a four leaf clover if you are able to find one. Make sure all the herbs you use are fully dried so they don’t mould.

Once all the ingredients are in the jar, burn a green candle on top of the lid to seal it. Then place it somewhere visible to act as a reminder to focus your intentions. 

As with all spell-work, use the tools and ingredients you have at your disposal. If you don’t have citrine and jade, use clear quartz or green aventurine instead. Go foraging for clover. An easy way to get mint is to buy pure mint tea bags from the supermarket and then split the bags to use the contents. If you can’t find one or more of the herbs, rosemary is a great substitute. 

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
✨𝕋𝕒𝕣𝕠𝕥 ℝ𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. The Six of Pentacles is a reminder of how much other people may need your help right now. You already give so much of your time and energy to others, but in the current worldwide situation, you may find that friends and family reach out to you more for practical help. Maybe they need food or medicines collected for them if they are self isolating or perhaps it’s more about offering emotional support by a telephone or video call. But here’s the good thing about this card, everything that you give, whether it be time, energy or monetary, will be returned back to you threefold. Your contribution will be highly valued by those who receive it. You have a very generous nature and you enjoy the good feelings associated with helping others, but be careful that your kind spirit does not get taken advantage of. Not everyone actually deserves the help you offer and some people can feel like a drain on your energy.

2. The reversed Ace of Swords is often an indicator of an inner breakthrough or idea, but be cautious about sharing details with others until you’ve had the time to clear your mind first. You need to have a clear plan about what you want to do, how you want to do it as well as what this inner change means to you. The most important question you must ask yourself is will your idea or breakthrough bring you closer to the things you want most? If the answer is ‘yes’ then explore how best to manifest this in the external world in the most effective way. If the answer is ‘no’ then don’t be scared to go back to the drawing board and rethink things through.

3. The World reversed can suggests you are seeking some kind of closure on a personal issue but you’re struggling. You know in your heart that in order to learn to accept and embrace where you are now, you must first let go of parts of your past that still have a negative impact upon you. You hold so much inside that you don’t mention and it’s time to release some of the mental pressure. Finding the closure you are looking for is likely to be a very personal journey, but it is one that will bring you multiple benefits and help you feel more balanced on an emotional level.

#witch

🪐 𝕍𝕠𝕚𝕕 𝕠𝕗 ℂ𝕠𝕦𝕣𝕤𝕖 🪐
This is literally a grey area in astrology. A Void of Course is the time when the moon is not in any zodiac sign as it passes between one sign and another. This time can be anything from a couple of seconds to a few days. 

Astrologists believe that during this time, we are more likely to have awkward encounters, be more forgetful (which I don’t think is possible with me 😂) and feel the need to slow down life a little bit. The world is turning and you just want to step off the treadmill for a while. Just go with it. 

It’s a great opportunity to just ‘be’ for a while, relax for a while. It’s not necessarily a time to begin anything new.

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
Happy Sunday! 🌞
I absolutely love sharing Witchy drawings and pictures, but I wanted to share Witchy art in other forms too. It’s such a good way to help inspire but also support smaller businesses, especially since Instagram has changed their algorithm (again) meaning so many amazing artists don’t get the recognition their work deserves. 

These are not paid ads in any way. This is just me, sharing the crafts and creations of those businesses I personally really love.

I wanted to start with Charlotte and Oliver at @artofnadar. I absolutely adore all their creations, all of which are decorating the wall around my altar (swipe left to see more). You can tell they really put their heart and souls into what they make, and they also are very local to me here in Yorkshire!

To buy, go to @artofnadar and click on the link to their website in their bio.

Have you got any favourite Witchy artists and/or creators? 

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
🧹 𝔽𝕝𝕪𝕚𝕟𝕘 𝕆𝕚𝕝 🧹
Flying oils or ointments have been used by practitioners of Witchcraft for hundreds of years. A flying oil is an hallucinogenic oil to aid in practices such as astral travel and spirit work. 

Recipes of flying oils have survived throughout the centuries and we are able to see what was used in them. Toxic Belladonna was a popular herb, which is something that modern flying oils generally don’t contain. 

Flying oils were traditionally made from rendered animal fat and some modern oils are made from this too. Thankfully, for us vegetarians and vegans, they can now be made from vegetable or sunflower oil. 

In the past, flying oils were used so the souls of the user could leave their bodies to fly in spirit to the Sabbath; or a hallucinatory 'trip' facilitated by the entheogenic effects of potent drugs absorbed through the skin. 

Have you ever used a flying oil?

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
✨S𝕖𝕝𝕗 C𝕒𝕣𝕖 R𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. W𝕣𝕚𝕥𝕖 A G𝕣𝕒𝕥𝕚𝕥𝕦𝕕𝕖 L𝕚𝕤𝕥
Sometimes we can get so busy and caught up in life that we forget to practice gratitude. It could be a person, a conversation, a kind gesture or the little things that make you smile it sitting and writing all these things down, however big or small can bring a sense of grounding as it shifts our minds to the present moment. It also allows us to take control of our thoughts. 

2. S𝕪𝕟𝕔 𝕨𝕚𝕥𝕙 𝕥𝕙𝕖 M𝕠𝕠𝕟
The moon is a powerful celestial body that reflects the flow of our lives and the phases we go through. With the full moon coming up, it’s a great time to reconnect. The full moon is when the moon is at the height of its power. Notice how it makes you feel. Start following the different phases of the moon as you move through the next 30 days. Research how the energies of the different phases can be used in you own life. 

3. T𝕒𝕜𝕖 𝕒 W𝕒𝕝𝕜
Go for a nature walk is a great way to get some exercise for your physical body but also to nourish mind and spirit too. Set some time aside each day to go for a walk, even if it’s just a short walk, it can boost your sense of well-being. Journal how this time makes you feel & the revelations & thoughts that come to you as a result. Notice how even a short walk can bring a sense of balance and can be incredibly grounding, which is important to us all, particularly if you’re an empath. Shake it up by visiting somewhere you haven’t been before to keep things interesting.
